comment:
You have basically ignored the judgment.  The way court works is the evidence is heard, weighed, tested and then a judge makes a decision on the balance of probabilities whether something happened or not.  In other words the judge found that there was more then a 50% chance that he was violent towards a woman.
This is not the right way to examine this case.  JD made a very bad decision to fight this case.  It was never a criminal case - but was run like one.  In fact the parameters were very narrow - all The Sun had to prove in Court, according to the civil standard - to win the case - was one thing only (whether actually true or not) - that is that there was a 51% chance that he struck AH at least once.  Prove that and The Sun would win its case.

This case was not about domestic violence and a contest between Team JD and Team AH.  Even if AH is a serious abuser, JD would lose this case unless he could prove that he never, not once, hit AH.  He rolled the dice and lost.  The poor guy needs to get clean and sober, hire a good publicist, sack his lawyers, withdraw his US litigation, and start doing activist work talking about how men can also be victims of domestic violence.
